==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horrent
<hw>Hor"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>horrens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>horrere</ets> to bristle. See
<er>Horror</er>.]</ety> <def>Standing erect, as bristles; covered with
bristling points; bristled; bristling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rough and <qex>horrent</qex> with figures in strong relief.</q>
<rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With bright emblazonry and <qex>horrent</qex> arms.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horrible</ent>⟦br⟧
